description.narrative: Output 3.3: Parents and caregivers have improved knowledge and skills to adopt essential nutrition practices, which contributes to Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: OUTCOME 3: Children, adolescent mothers and women, particularly in vulnerable and deprived areas, have increased access to quality services and information, and adopt appropriate nutritional practices to prevent and treat malnutrition
